{
  "text": "More generally, if V is a representation space of K and V M is the associated vector bundle, every element u \u2208 Q defines tautologically a linear isomorphism between V and V M \u03c0(u) and every section \u03c3 of V M determines a V -valued function\u03c3 on Q defined by\u03c3(u) := u \u22121 \u03c3 \u03c0(u) . The covariant derivative on V M induced by \u03b1 satisfies [CITATION_1] (",
